1 AN ACT relating to the foster care system.
2 WHEREAS, the Commonwealth has a responsibility to protect the safety and well-
3 being of children in the foster care system; and
4 WHEREAS, repeated placement changes and inappropriate temporary housing,
5 including the use of cars, offices, and hotel rooms, lead to severe emotional,
6 psychological, and developmental harm; and
7 WHEREAS, stable, long-term placements increase the likelihood of successful
8 outcomes for foster children, including higher educational attainment, improved mental
9 health, and reduced homelessness; and
10 WHEREAS, a lack of sufficient placement options may lead to harmful and
11 unstable temporary placements; and
12 WHEREAS, prioritizing kinship care, foster families, and group homes will create a
13 safer, more supportive environment for foster children; and
14 WHEREAS, the ability to track a foster child's locations in real time ensures the
15 foster child's safety and prevents instances of a child going missing while in custody;
16 NOW, THEREFORE,
17 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
18 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 199 IS CREATED TO
19 READ AS FOLLOWS:
20 (1) A child in foster care shall not be housed in the following conditions, except in
21 emergency situations not exceeding twenty-four (24) hours:
22 (a) Vehicles, including but not limited to cars, vans, and buses;
23 (b) State or cabinet offices; or
24 (c) Hotels, motels, or short-term rentals.
25 (2) A child in foster care shall be placed in one (1) of the following:
26 (a) A fictive kin placement;
27 (b) A kinship care placement;
Page 1 of 3
