UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1842
1 (c) A licensed foster family home; or
2 (d) A Licensed child-caring facility.
3 (3) A child in foster care shall not be moved more than two (2) times in a twelve (12)
4 month period unless extenuating circumstances such as safety concerns or
5 reunification efforts necessitate the change.
6 (4) An employee of the cabinet shall provide a written explanation for any placement
7 change beyond the initial placement to the secretary, and the placement change
8 shall be approved by the secretary.
9 (5) The department shall promulgate administrative regulations in accordance KRS
10 Chapter 13A to implement this section and to minimize placement disruptions
11 and prioritize stability .
12 Section 2. KRS 620.320 is amended to read as follows:
13 The duties of the State Citizen Foster Care Review Board shall be to:
14 (1) Establish, approve, and provide training programs for local citizen foster care
15 review board members;
16 (2) Review and coordinate the activities of local citizen foster care review boards;
17 (3) Establish reporting procedures to be followed by the local citizen foster care review
18 boards and publish an annual written report compiling data reported by local foster
19 care review boards which shall include statistics relating, at a minimum, to the
20 following:
21 (a) Barriers to permanency identified in reviews;
22 (b) The number of children moved more than two[three] (2)[(3)] times within a
23 twelve[six] (12)[(6)] month period;
24 (c) The average length of time in care;
25 (d) Local solutions reported to meet identified barriers; and
26 (e) The total number and frequency of reviews;
27 (4) Publish an annual written report on the effectiveness of such local citizen foster
